<section style="padding:3rem 0; border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;">
  <div class="container" style="max-width:900px; margin:0 auto;">
    <h2>Why MIND?</h2>
    <p>
      Today, AI systems are split across Python notebooks, C++ runtimes, and hand-tuned CUDA.
      MIND collapses that into a single language and compiler pipeline.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Single language</strong> from prototype to production with one deterministic toolchain.</li>
      <li><strong>Tensor-native types</strong> with shape and dtype checked at compile time.</li>
      <li><strong>Built-in autodiff</strong> over a static SSA IR, not a dynamic tape bolted on top.</li>
      <li><strong>MLIR + LLVM pipeline</strong> for CPU, GPU, and future accelerators.</li>
      <li><strong>Open-core</strong>: language and compiler under Apache 2.0, production runtime as an optional commercial add-on.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

